The Nasarawa State House of Assembly yesterday re-elected Alhaji Ibrahim Balarabe-Abdullahi the Speaker of the sixth Assembly. He was unopposed. The Speaker was sworn in Lafia, the state capital, by the Clerk of the Assembly, Mr Ego Maikeffi Abashe. Nehemiah Tsetse Dandaura (APC), the member representing Akwanga North, was elected Deputy Speaker and returned unopposed. Mohammed Okpoku (APC, Udege/Loko) nominated Balarabe-Abdullahi and was seconded by Aliyu Dogara (APC, Wamba). Okpoku said the nomination of Balarabe-Abdullahi was based on his leadership qualities and track records. Also, Alhaji Mohammed Muluku (APC, Nassarawa Eggon East) nominated Tsetse Dandaura from Akwanga North for the position of Deputy Speaker. Danladi Jatau (PDP-Kokona West) seconded the nomination. In his acceptance speech, Balarabe-Abdullahi expressed appreciation to his colleagues for the privilege to serve them again. “I am on my feet to accept my nomination and election as Speaker of the sixth Assembly. “I consider my nomination as affirmation of my leadership in the last fifth Assembly,” he said.